## Design System

- Use a utility-first CSS approach with [Tailwind CSS](mdc:package.json)
- Follow a consistent color palette defined in `global.css`
- Maintain responsive design for all components: mobile, tablet, and desktop
- Use the color schemes as defined in figma.
- Use the following breakpoints:
  - Mobile: < 640px
  - Tablet: 640px - 1024px
  - Desktop: > 1024px

## Typography

- Use a consistent type scale defined in the theme configuration
- Font family: 
  - Primary: Inter (sans-serif)
- Font weights:
  - Regular: 400
  - Medium: 500
  - Bold: 700
- Heading sizes
  - Desktop: 64px, 48px, 32px, 24px
  - Mobile: 36px, 32px, 24px, 20px
- Text sizes
  - Desktop: 24px, 20px, 18px, 16px, 14px
  - Mobile: 24px, 18px, 16px, 14px

## Components Styling

- Prefer Tailwind CSS utility classes for component styling
- For complex components, use class variance authority for different variants
- Use CSS variables for theme values that need runtime changes
- Keep consistent spacing as defined in figma
- Use shadows and elevation consistently according to the figma


## Icons and Images

- Download svg from figma and use it directly with svgr plugin
- Use SVG icons whenever possible
- Optimize images for web (compression, proper formats)
- Implement responsive images with srcset when necessary
- Use lazy loading for images below the fold

